        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Achilles Tendonitis is inflammation of the Achilles tendon, which can lead to degeneration. The Achilles tendon, a large tendon at the back of the leg that attaches to the heel, can become painful due to this condition.<br/><br/>Pain from Achilles Tendonitis can develop gradually without any history of trauma and may present as shooting, burning, or piercing pain. Untreated Achilles Tendonitis poses a risk of the tendon becoming weak and potentially rupturing.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
